spans.text: Where warbled , ever free from care , The winged musicians of the air
warbled , ever free from care , The winged musicians of the air
agree To join the sylvan harmony
while they As sweetly billed their time away
To bear the one , when one was flown
When thirsty , in the shallow rills Together dipped their little bills
The fiery mate and chirping scold
a pair , So kind as he , as she so fair
all the honey of their mind
